The Head of Consumer Liability Products of Diamond Bank, Mr. Osita Ede, has assured that the bank’s ongoing business combination deal with Access Bank will bring about a stronger institution that will sustain the product promises that are beneficial to customers. Mr. Ede who gave the assurance in a media interview, said, “We have looked at all that and it is going to be a bigger Diamondxtra. Diamondxtra stays the way it is. Some of the concerns have been coming up with regards to customers who won prizes like ‘Salary for Life’. We see some of those questions in the social media asking, ‘What happens to them?’ So, the message we want to go out there and give is that nothing changes. As deadline for bank verification number draws near MTN partners Diamond Bank on new offer Mixed reactions trail Diamond Bank merger with Access Bank